  1. No answer and not too happy both had the lowest rate of married responders in their categories. Both these categories had high numbers of divorces as well. Meanwhile not applicable and very happy both had the greatest number of marries responders in their categories. This shows that married tend to be the happiest while divorced or widowed are the least happy which makes sense.

library('ggplot2')

  1. The highest mean years of education is for those who answered with no answer. Never married has on average about .4 more years of education than married. While seperateds average is more than 1 whole year below married and widowed is nearly two. The low years of education for widowed could imply the military is involved. This could show people chose to go to the military rather than normal school.
